        body: "Look up from the screen. Pick one room. Count the elements that are functional because of what they <em>aren't</em>: a door (a wall that isn't there), a window (a wall that isn't there), the inside of a cup, the space between books on a shelf, the airway in your nose. Stop counting at twelve. Chapter 11's claim is that twelve was reached very quickly."
